      },
      "date": "2013-07-05 09:41:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nshouldn't ll_atomic_open() set IT_CREATE by 'open_flags & O_CREAT' instead of mode? because according to `man 2 open` if O_CREATE is not set mode is ignored.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "8d8b4aecfd43e4b1b0df81b4234d075cfebb7b63",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-05 15:01:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nLai, I believe you're correct. Perhaps mode will always be passed as zero if O_CREAT is clear though. So we could test with a 3.6 or later client doing open creates with a zero mode.\n\nhttp://lxr.free-electrons.com/source/fs/cifs/dir.c#L408\nhttp://lxr.free-electrons.com/source/fs/fuse/dir.c#L506",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
