          {
            "commit": "69f000d420d01c48fb7300ff973e498f2dbf92b5",
            "subject": "LU-3079 osd-zfs: Change header order to avoid build fail"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-07-01 17:26:15.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-07-26 17:57:15.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-3517 llite: don't check for O_CREAT in it_create_mode",
        "message": "LU-3517 llite: don't check for O_CREAT in it_create_mode\n\nll_lookup_it() checks for O_CREAT in struct lookup_intent's\nit_create_mode member which is nonsensical, as it_create_mode is used\nfor file mode bits (S_IFREG, S_IRUSR, ...). Fix this by just checking\nfor IT_CREATE in it_op and do the same in llu_lookup_it(). This will\nnot affect the behavior of either function, since if O_CREATE (0100)\nis actually set in o_create_mode then IT_CREATE must have been set in\nit_op. In ll_atomic_open() check for O_CREAT in the open_flags\nparameter rather than testing mode.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I301964222ec043e6f0cc3b000678fe3c881a2381\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/6786\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>\nTested-by: Hudson\nTested-by: Maloo <whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
